June 18, 2020

Dear PRBLA Parents/Guardians,

All cadets entering 7th grade are required to have Tdap and Meningitis vaccines. HPV vaccine is also recommended for rising 7th graders. In addition, a new N.C. law now requires rising 12th graders to have a booster dose of the Meningitis vaccine. As required by law, these cadets must have these vaccines within 30 days of starting school.

Keisha White,
Superintendent

The State Board of Education (SBE) and NC Department of Public Instruction (NCDPI), in consultation with the North Carolina Department of Health and Human Services (NCDHHS), have developed Lighting Our Way Forward: North Carolina's Guidebook for Reopening Public Schools in response to the COVID-19 public health crisis. The purpose of this guidance document is to support NC public schools and communities in developing their plans and strategies for reopening schools in the 2020-21 school year. As public school units (PSUs) work to operationalize these recommendations, it is critical to be intentional and prepared for change as the year unfolds in light of public health needs.

There are still slots available for the 20-21 school year.

post_text: The 7th Corps of Cadets would like to thank all warriors serving on the “Tip of the Spear” on this Armed Forces Day! A special thank you to Keyanna Cann PBLA19 and Kalil Richardson PBLA 18 who are still proudly serving.
text: The 7th Corps of Cadets would like to thank all warriors serving on the “Tip of the Spear” on this Armed Forces Day! A special thank you to Keyanna Cann PBLA19 and Kalil Richardson PBLA 18 who are still proudly serving.

post_text:
Today is National Peace Officers Memorial Day. In 1961 President John F. Kennedy asked Congress to designate 15 May as Police officers Memorial Day. We honor officers that have fallen while serving on the Blue line that keeps us all safe. The sacrifice that you and your families have made is not forgotten and taken lightly.
The 7th Corps of Cadets uses 15 May to salute the fallen but we also use it to honor law enforcement officers who are still serving. Thank you to all law endowment personnel everywhere. Even though we are based in Bladen County thank you to the Sherriffs offices of Columbus, Cumberland, Hoke and Robeson County. The police departments of Hope Mills, Fayetteville, Lake Waccamaw and Lumberton. A special thanks to the Bladenboro, Elizabethtown, Whitelake police departments, the Bladen County Sheriffs Office and the North Carolina State Highway Patrol. Thank you all for keeping our cadets and their families safe. Until we can gather again next year stay safe.

post_text: Founders day memories!
shared_text:
Paul R. Brown Leadership Academy is at Paul R Brown Leadership Academy.
April 16, 2016 at 9:25 AM · Elizabethtown, NC ·

The Paul R. Brown Leadership Academy's 3rd Corps of Cadets celebrated Founders Day. The day started with a briefing by Lieutenant Commander John Trioli of the United States Navy Sea Cadet Corps. The Corps participated in a Review at the end of the day. We were fortunate to have the St John's Northwestern Pipe and Drum Band here to take part in the ceremony. At the conclusion of the Review the Pipes and Drums put on a mini concert for parents and cadets. Thank you to our parents and supporters for your patience yesterday. Also thank you to the Cadets of SJNMA for being the highlight of the Founders Day Ceremony. As always you have been there for your little brothers and sisters.

Parents if you are coming to witness the crowning of the queen or her court you must be in the same minimum standard appropriate attire.

National Society of Black/Jacks Company Bravo-4
September 14, 2019 at 5:43 PM ·

September 13 is the birthday of General of the The Armies John Joseph Blackjack Pershing. The brothers and sisters of The Paul R. Brown Leadership Academy Blackjack chapter Company Bravo-4 celebrated General Pershing’s birthday after school. The cadets conducted a wreath laying ceremony. After the ceremony the Company had a birthday dinner at Red Robin in his honor.

post_text: ‪Parents we have been following the storm and will amend our schedule. Tomorrow there will be no drill & ceremonies. We will send the Cadets home at noon. If we wait until our regular scheduled departure time our Cadets who live in Columbus County will experience the first bands of the storm. We will be closed Thursday and Friday. The school reopening will be dictated by the school having power and every Cadet being accessible safely by bus. Please like and follow our page so that we can keep you updated. Remember we serve five counties we must make sure that all Cadets can travel back and forth safely.
text: ‪Parents we have been following the storm and will amend our schedule. Tomorrow there will be no drill & ceremonies. We will send the Cadets home at noon. If we wait until our regular scheduled departure time our Cadets who live in Columbus County will experience the first bands of the storm. We will be closed Thursday and Friday. The school reopening will be dictated by the school having power and every Cadet being accessible safely by bus. Please like and follow our page so that we can keep you updated. Remember we serve five counties we must make sure that all Cadets can travel back and forth safely.

post_text:
We will monitor the storm and make a weather call once we have more information. To our new parents we will not be shutting down when the local schools shut down. Remember many of them become shelters for the Red Cross. They can not become shelters until the students are home. Also remember we serve five counties and our decision is based on every Cadet being able to get home safely. We will monitor the storm and make a decision later this week.

The uniform for the week is as follows:
Tuesday - OGS

Wednesday - Class Gray/$3.00 dress down to support the Cadets interested in attending the symphony. Appropriate civilian attire only. No slides or crocs, no ripped jeans or clothes, and no joggers. It is better to ask than pretend not to know.

Thursday - OGs for RCTs/CDTs, ACU Cadre and NWU’s for Sea Cadets.

Friday - Summer Class Gray

Saturday - Saturday Academy Summer Class Gray.
Corps Day Dance Casual attire

post_text: New Cadet training begins tomorrow. Parents can bring their Cadets starting at 0715. Parents please have your Cadet wear one of their white T-shirts. Also they need to wear athletic shoes and a pair of their black socks. Please have them leave their jewelry home they will not need it. The only necklaces and bracelets that are authorized are medic alerts. Female Cadets may have one pair of earrings that are ball(gold or silver), post, stud or diamond. They can not exceed 1/4 of an inch. Remember if they are bringing their lunch it must be in their own lunchbox. All high school males are to be clean shaven. Female Cadets have your hair up and off the collar. If your Cadet needs a haircut they can bring six dollars and we will take them to the barber. They do not need book bags tomorrow. We will see you in the morning.
